That’s the issue.

With only @InjectMocks, cosStorageService is a real object, not a Mockito mock/spy, so this will not work:

doNothing().when(cosStorageService).moveFile(sourceKey, targetKey);
verify(cosStorageService).moveFile(sourceKey, targetKey);

Two ways to fix it

Option 1 — use @Spy @InjectMocks for cosStorageService

This is the easiest if you want to verify moveFile(...) directly.

Change:

@InjectMocks
private CosStorageService cosStorageService;

to:

@Spy
@InjectMocks
private CosStorageService cosStorageService;

Then the tests I gave will work.

⸻

Option 2 — keep @InjectMocks only, and verify downstream S3 calls

This is usually better if you want to test behavior, not internal method calls.

Since moveIfExists(...) now calls moveFile(...), and moveFile(...) eventually calls S3 operations, verify those S3 interactions instead.

